                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14104183" author="mgrover" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 18:38:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, Mani. Should &lt;tt&gt;if [ -d &quot;/usr/lib/hive-hcatalog&quot; ]; then&lt;/tt&gt; be an else if instead?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104522" author="mnarayan" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 21:36:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for taking a look at this Mark.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if [ -d &quot;/usr/lib/hive-hcatalog&quot; ]; looks right to me. We only want to check for the existence of this directory if HCAT_HOME is not set. Right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104586" author="mgrover" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 22:07:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;But, if &lt;tt&gt;/usr/lib/hcatalog&lt;/tt&gt; already exists, should we still go through this check? What should happen in the corner case where both &lt;tt&gt;/usr/lib/hcatalog&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;/usr/lib/hive-hcatalog&lt;/tt&gt; exist (say because 2 versions of HCatalog are installed, one from pre-hive times and one from after the project was merged into Hive?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104664" author="mgrover" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 22:54:23 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 (non-committer)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104670" author="mnarayan" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 22:57:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The first patch replaced checking for /usr/lib/hcatalog with /usr/lib/hive-hcatalog so, if we had both versions of HCatalog side by side I think it would have still worked. But, I agree that if the user only has the previous version installed, this check would have not set the HCAT_HOME and exited incorrectly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks! Updated patch. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104811" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 00:48:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. Will commit it shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14104839" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 21 Aug 2014 01:16:50 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk and 0.13 branch. Thank you guys!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
